= First <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span> Party Congress

The <span style="color: #FFCC00;">Liberal People's Party</span> (<span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>) has officially been founded! Hans Luther, former chancellor and <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> member, has been chosen as the interim leader of the new party.

The <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>'s inaugural congress will play a major role in shaping the direction of the newly founded party, and most importantly, decide who will lead the liberal movement forward. [? if lvp_ideology == "Right": Disappointingly, the right-wing shift of the predecessor parties has impacted this party as well. ?]

- @luther: The party votes...

@luther
call: lvp_formed
on-arrival: lvp_relation += 5; lvp_left += 3
face-image: img/portraits/luther.jpg

Hans Luther is chosen to lead the <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>, a long-time advocate for liberal and bourgeois unity, and a figure acceptable to both wings of the newly unified party. His influence among the German business community undoubtedly is what secured him the selection, it's hard to imagine the mixture of the dissenting factions of both predecessor parties being able to choose a single candidate.

Meanwhile, the skeptics on the extremes of the party, despite their initial resistance to the merger, is now focusing on shifting the <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span> further towards one end of the political spectrum. The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> right will leverage the highly influential support of the party's industrial backers, while the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> left will attempt to lobby for policy that benefits the working class with their supporters in the labor unions.

